<title>UK: TABLE-Euromoney H1 profit rises 5.0 pct.</title>
<headline>TABLE-Euromoney H1 profit rises 5.0 pct.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months to March 31</p>
<p>			 (million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Shr (pence)		35.66		  vs 31.96</p>
<p> Dividend (pence)	 18.0		   vs 14.0</p>
<p> Pretax		     12.0		   vs 11.5</p>
<p> Turnover		   49.5		   vs 52.1</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said its results justified an increase of 1.75p in the interim dividend to 15.75p per share. However, Euromoney raised the dividend by 4.0p as a result of its decision to reduce the difference between its interim and final payouts.</p>
<p>Year-ago pretax profit included a gain of 1.5 million stg on the sale of certain operations.</p>
<p>Full company name - Euromoney Publications Plc. -- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717</p>
